N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 19 ยง 260.5 - Notice of expiration

State Regulations
(a) Whenever a notice of proposed rule making has expired, the Department of State
shall prepare and publish a notice of expiration as soon as
practicable. (b) Whenever a notice
of expiration is published in the State Register, the expired notice of
proposed rule making shall be deleted from the State Register's action pending
index. Notes
